						               													<description>Space Clash is a non-collectible card game for 2 - 4 interplanetary warlords in which each player chooses one out of four exciting races, each being represented by a well balanced deck of 40 cards featuring unique gameplay, and tries to lead his &amp;#10;race to different ways of victory, be it by total military annihilation of the enemy or by cultural domination.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Space Clash, many roads lead to victory, the goal being to deplete the opponent's 40 card deck. When a player is required to draw a card from their Supply (deck) but cannot because it is empty, the player immediately loses the game. For each damage a player takes through attacks or card effects, they have to discard the topmost card from their Supply to their Junkyard (discard pile).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game features the tried and tested &amp;quot;Clash Game System&amp;quot; created by Andreas Propst, which features 3 major characteristics:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;a) Deck depletion as the primary win condition.&amp;#10;b) A resource system in which you will be building stacks of resource cards to play your non-Resource cards onto&amp;#10;c) Different Zones for different types of cards with specific implications on the cards, depending on which zone they are in&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Build up your industry, construct spaceships to attack your opponents or to defend against enemy attacks, train&amp;#10;personnel like ship crews, researchers, diplomats and spies, research new technology or try to dominate through diplomacy &amp;#10;or dodgy schemes and political intrigue.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The possibilities in Space Clash are countless...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Which race will you choose?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The versatile and inventive Terrans, who are able to adapt well to any challenge they might face?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The reptilian warrior race of the Skaargans, with their supreme ability to construct, mend and salvage?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The dodgy and scheming Intrazi, who have perfected the art of telepathy, becoming the masters of secrets?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Or the ancient and mysterious Attrayids who are rather passive but excell in gathering wisdom and knowledge?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Choose your race and lead it to victory by carefully planning your strategy and making the best use of the their&amp;#10;unique strenghtes and abilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
